              <div id="monetate-content-1">
              </div>
              <div class="branding">
               <div class="branding-testimonial">
                <h3 class="branding-testimonial-title">
                 What Customers Are Saying...
                </h3>
                <p class="branding-testimonial-info">
                 I needed to switch over to Apple computer, phone and ipad because of software changes in my buisness.

I was able to purchase a Macbook Air, Iphone 5se, and Ipad Air.
These items were either open box or refurbished with a A rating.  Fabulous Prices, all worked and looked new.  I am a faithful user of a  popular on line store that deals in the same items, however I can not get these kind of deals especially at these condition and prices.
                 <br/>
                 <a class="link-more" href="https://www.newegg.com/d/Info/Testimonials">
                  <span>
                   See All
                  </span>
                  <i aria-label="more" class="fa fa-caret-right">
                  </i>
                 </a>
                </p>
               </div>
               <div class="branding-features">
                <div class="branding-featured">
                 <a class="branding-featured-img" href="https://www.newegg.com/promotions/nepro/18-1881/index.html?cm_sp=newegg-store-credit-card-_-categorypages-_-whatrtheysaying--_-NA-_-NA" title="12 Months Special Financing** every day on purchases of $499 or more.">
                  <img alt="12 Months Special Financing** every day on purchases of $499 or more." src="//images10.newegg.com/WebResource/Themes/2005/Nest/branding_cc.png"/>
                 </a>
                 <h3>
                  12 Months Special Financing** every day on purchases of $499 or more.
                 </h3>
                 <a class="link-more" href="https://www.newegg.com/promotions/nepro/18-1881/index.html?cm_sp=newegg-store-credit-card-_-categorypages-_-whatrtheysaying--_-NA-_-NA" title="12 Months Special Financing** every day on purchases of $499 or more.">
                  <span>
                   Learn More
                  </span>
                  <i aria-label="more" class="fa fa-caret-right">
                  </i>
                 </a>
                </div>
               </div>
              </div>
             </div>
             <div id="SEO">
              <p>
               Desktop graphics cards matter much more than the CPU when it comes to both building and buying a gaming PC. There's a lot to consider when picking out computer graphics cards, from the PC case size to the type of monitor on the system to the gameplay settings you're looking to use. All in all, the most important thing is to make sure you can use it before you buy it.
              </p>
              <h2 class="article-title-third">
               NVIDIA and AMD Computer Graphics Cards Offer Key Features
              </h2>
              There are numerous desktop graphics cards from several different manufacturers, including
              <a href="//www.newegg.com/Video-Cards-Video-Devices/Category/ID-38">
               video cards
              </a>
              . However, there are only two corporations, AMD and NVIDIA®, that manufacture the GPUs that are used in these components. Intel® is looking to make their way into the computer graphics cards realm very soon. AMD offers budget and competitive upper-mid range GPUs, and their latest Radeon RX series is now toe-to-toe, in terms of power consumption, with their NVIDIA counterparts. Check for available
              <a href="//www.newegg.com/Video-Cards-Video-Devices/Category/ID-38">
               video card accessories
              </a>
              to factor in their impact on your build.
              <h2 class="article-title-third">
               The Importance of Form Factor for Gaming Graphics Cards
              </h2>
              One thing you should keep in mind is that it's vital the case has enough room for the card you want. Look at the thickness, height and length of the case. Desktop graphics cards can be found in a triple shot, dual shot or single shot option. Many of these types of graphics cards will take up two expansion ports, and will be full height. Even though a card typically only takes up 1 or 2 ports in the case, if it's got a fan shroud and a big heatsink, then it can end up blocking an adjacent slot.
              <h2 class="article-title-third">
               Look At the Power Connectors for Compatible Power Supply
              </h2>
              <p>
               Most top-notch gaming graphics cards use a lot more than the 75-watt maximum standard provided by PCIe slots. Such cards will need you to connect supplemental power connectors that usually come in 8-pin and 6-pin varieties. If you have a power supply that does not have the supplemental power connectors you require, then you might need to get an adapter that sources power from a few Molex or SATA connectors. The next logical step is to upgrade.
              </p>
              <h2 class="article-title-third">
               Match the Graphics Card to Virtual Reality Usage
              </h2>
              <p>
               If you intend to use PC VR platforms, video graphics cards are an important element. then you'll need to use, at the very least, mid-range
               <a href="//www.newegg.com/Workstation-Graphics-Cards/SubCategory/ID-449">
                workstation graphics cards
               </a>
               that have optimal performance levels. In fact, you just might want to concentrate on the high-end models of
               <a href="//www.newegg.com/Video-Cards-Video-Devices/Category/ID-38">
                video cards
               </a>
               , like the NVIDIA devices. These are well-known to support virtual reality gaming. There are some lower cost options you can use. The Radeon RX family of cards from AMD offer substantial power and response for virtual reality performance. However, most seasoned gamers will advise you to go for the top-tier desktop graphics cards if you're looking for seamless virtual reality gaming.
              </p>
             </div>
            </div>
           </div>
          </div>
         </div>
        </div>
       </div>
      </div>
     </div>
    </section>

There's a lot to consider when picking out computer graphics cards, from the PC case size to the type of monitor on the system to the gameplay settings you're looking to use. All in all, the most important thing is to make sure you can use it before you buy it.\u003C\u002Fp\u003E\u003Ch2 class=\"article-title-third\"\u003ENVIDIA and AMD Computer Graphics Cards Offer Key Features\u003C\u002Fh2\u003EThere are numerous desktop graphics cards from several different manufacturers, including \u003Ca href=\"\u002F\u002Fwww.newegg.com\u002FVideo-Cards-Video-Devices\u002FCategory\u002FID-38\"\u003Evideo cards\u003C\u002Fa\u003E. However, there are only two corporations, AMD and NVIDIA®, that manufacture the GPUs that are used in these components. Intel® is looking to make their way into the computer graphics cards realm very soon. AMD offers budget and competitive upper-mid range GPUs, and their latest Radeon RX series is now toe-to-toe, in terms of power consumption, with their NVIDIA counterparts. Check for available \u003Ca href=\"\u002F\u002Fwww.newegg.com\u002FVideo-Cards-Video-Devices\u002FCategory\u002FID-38\"\u003Evideo card accessories\u003C\u002Fa\u003E to factor in their impact on your build.  \u003Ch2 class=\"article-title-third\"\u003EThe Importance of Form Factor for Gaming Graphics Cards\u003C\u002Fh2\u003EOne thing you should keep in mind is that it's vital the case has enough room for the card you want. Look at the thickness, height and length of the case. Desktop graphics cards can be found in a triple shot, dual shot or single shot option. Many of these types of graphics cards will take up two expansion ports, and will be full height. Even though a card typically only takes up 1 or 2 ports in the case, if it's got a fan shroud and a big heatsink, then it can end up blocking an adjacent slot.\u003Ch2 class=\"article-title-third\"\u003ELook At the Power Connectors for Compatible Power Supply\u003C\u002Fh2\u003E\u003Cp\u003EMost top-notch gaming graphics cards use a lot more than the 75-watt maximum standard provided by PCIe slots. Such cards will need you to connect supplemental power connectors that usually come in 8-pin and 6-pin varieties. If you have a power supply that does not have the supplemental power connectors you require, then you might need to get an adapter that sources power from a few Molex or SATA connectors. The next logical step is to upgrade.\u003C\u002Fp\u003E\u003Ch2 class=\"article-title-third\"\u003EMatch the Graphics Card to Virtual Reality Usage\u003C\u002Fh2\u003E\u003Cp\u003EIf you intend to use PC VR platforms, video graphics cards are an important element. then you'll need to use, at the very least, mid-range \u003Ca href=\"\u002F\u002Fwww.newegg.com\u002FWorkstation-Graphics-Cards\u002FSubCategory\u002FID-449\"\u003Eworkstation graphics cards\u003C\u002Fa\u003E that have optimal performance levels. In fact, you just might want to concentrate on the high-end models of \u003Ca href=\"\u002F\u002Fwww.newegg.com\u002FVideo-Cards-Video-Devices\u002FCategory\u002FID-38\"\u003Evideo cards\u003C\u002Fa\u003E, like the NVIDIA devices. These are well-known to support virtual reality gaming. There are some lower cost options you can use. The Radeon RX family of cards from AMD offer substantial power and response for virtual reality performance. However, most seasoned gamers will advise you to go for the top-tier desktop graphics cards if you're looking for seamless virtual reality gaming.\u003C\u002Fp\u003E"},"AdobeTrackingMessage":{"Flag":"dominated"},"CustomerHtmlCode":null,"JssUrl":null}
